  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are various legal frameworks to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk transactions\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Specific Industries Covered\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory approaches.",
